reviewText: 80-76%-perfect75-71%-awsome70-66%-good65-61%-poor60-56%-awful1. HECTOR, CHAVO & MONDO GUERRERO vs CACTUS JACK & THE RPM's (AWA SuperClash 3. December-13, 1988- In this match edie does not wrestle or even appere which makes this match interesting. I liked the pace and it seemed like the right way to go with an old school match. About a 7 minute macth and i wish foley could have got in more here. WInners HECTOR, CHAVO & MONDO GUERRERO. MAtch Rating 7/10.2. EDDIE GUERRERO & `LOVE MACHINE' ART BARR vs OCTAGON & EL HIJO SANTO (AAA When Worlds Collide. November-6, 1994): This is a 2 out of 3 falls `Hair vs Mask' match from one of the most famous ppv cards of the 1990's. But the rules are weird in that both members of a team being pinned equals 1 fall. How the hell can 2 pinfalls be classified as 1 fall!?!?!? Eddie is terrific in this match & opens up tremendously. Barr is not far behind him & is the proverbial heat machine. They dominate the early going & pin both their opponents to get the first fall by the 4 minute mark! The heels continue to dominate in the 2nd fall, but Octagon scores 2 quick pinfalls literally out of nowhere to even the score at the 11 minute mark. The 3rd & final fall thankfully adds some time to the match & there is some sensational spots. However, it's also a total mess in some respects. I understand that Lucha Libre has some different tagging rules, but I didn't think you could just walk in whenever you wanted to, in full view of the referee!The result is also just too unbelievable as each face beats 2 men despite being dominated to that point in time. While the match lasts 22 minutes on the DVD, it should be noted that an edit of some length is included. Terribly hard to rate, but too much confusion & unbelievability to rate too highly. Eddie is terrific though, showing his pace at the beginning, while highlighting his suplexes in his final showdown with Santo. Barr is also great with a variety of moves (dropkicks, frog splash & jumping tombstone piledriver) that definitely caught my eye. Don't let the match rating suggest that this bout shouldn't be on this DVD. It most definitely fits perfectly. Winners EDDIE GUERRERO & `LOVE MACHINE' ART BARR. Match Rating 8/10.3. reviewText: This dvd is not the best example of Eddie. The documentary on him is from a speical on UPN and not really well made. There are ten matches and most of them have been seen elsewhere. Now that Eddie's passed on, maybe WWE will re-release this set with better matchs and a better biography. Its sad how WWE has used Eddie's name on tv to get the heels some real heat. Eddie always promised to steal the show and he delivered. The best match ive ever witnessed him wrestle will not be on a dvd set. It was a house show I attended the year he died a few weeks away from SummerSlam. He wrestled Rey Mysterio in a falls count anywhere match and those two tore it up all over the building. Eddie got kicked in the face with a chair and bleed a gusher. No one knew how he pulled it off. Afterwards he got on the mic and said Dominic is still my son or something to that degree. It felt speical even though it was a house show. Again, a decent set for now but hopefully they'll make a better one.

reviewText: Hey cool, one of my favorite wrestlers gets his own DVD! Along with the matches, this has a 45min documentery about Latino Heat's career, showing how low he got (more than once) but how he's come back up to become one of the greatest wrestlers in the world today. A GREAT extra is that the documentery and ALL the matches are also available in Spanish! Also there's added commentary with Guerrero, Malenko, RVD and Rey Jr. on selected matches.Matches:1. Hector, Chavo & Mando Guerrero Vs. Cactus Jack & Rock N' Roll RPMs - AWA (Well WCCW actually) - Pretty fun match with some neat highspots for the time ** out of 52. Eddie Guerrero & Art Barr vs. El Hijo Del Santo & Octagon - A lot of people name this as one of the greatest Mexican matches ever. Octagon and Hijo del Santo put their legendary masks on the line against the hair of the hottest tag team at the time: Guerrero & Barr. ****3. Eddie Guerrero Vs. Dean Malenko - 2 out of 3 Falls - Before departing to WCW, these two put out another mat classic for the ECW crowd *****4. Eddie Guerrero Vs. Chris Jericho - Awesome battle that makes me remember just how cool WCW's Cruiserweight division was! ****5. Eddie Guerrero Vs. Rey Mysterio Jr. - Maybe the best cruiserweight match EVER with Mysterio putting his mask on the line against Guerrero's title *****6. Eddie Guerrero Vs. Chavo Guerrero - Started off as Stevie Ray Vs. Chavo, but Chavo wigs out and calls out Uncle Eddie in a hair vs. hair match. ***1/27. Eddie Guerrero Vs. Rob Van Dam - Ladder match - Mega-Awesome RAW Ladder match for the IC title. They cut out the part where a fan jumps in the ring. They should've kept it and then shown the beating he took by security.. With alternate commentary :-) ****1/28. Eddie & Chavo Vs. Angle & Benoit Vs. Edge & Rey Msyterio Jr. - Elimination match for the SD Tag title ****9. Eddie Guerrero Vs. Chris Benoit - U.S. Title tournament final - Benoit. Guerrero. What else has to be said? ****1/210. Eddie Guerrero Vs. Brock Lensar - SD World Championship - The Unstoppable Brock Lenar was on his way to defend the Championship against either Goldberg or Kurt Angle at WMXX, unfortunatly for him he had to meet Guerrero a month before. A perfect match to end the DVD with! ****1/2This is a great DVD to get if your a wrestling fan. I would've like to have seen the Guerrero/Edge (No DQ-My MOTY 02') or Guerrero/Ohtani match, but that's just me being a spoiled mark. This DVD has everything you need! Now when's that Bret Hart DVD coming out Vince?

reviewText: I can't even attempt to summerize Eddie Guerrero in a few words because I can't add anything to his legacy & reputation as not only a role model for overcoming dangerous demons & addictions and being proof that anybody can change their life for the better but as an inring competitor with heart & unbelievable ability that made up for his "lack of size" & any other sterotype that would prevent a smaller man from being a World Champion.  This is the story of the man who's famously known as "Latino Heat" in Eddie Guerrero.The documentry begins showing the Guerrero family free & talking about growing up around wrestling in El Paso, TX to the point where Eddie trained in his backyard & wrestled Chavo during the intermission of wrestling shows at 9 years old.  The importance of the lowrider to Eddie is touched upon before going into the story behind his relationship with Vickie.  How Eddie turned pro at age 16 and the importance of his time in New Japan, ECW, and WCW were talked about before getting into the story behind his car accident and his heavy drug addiction that almost took his live various times.  His move to WWE & the "Latino Heat" character were talked about before going into what led to his departure in 2001 & his marriage problems before they went into how he was able turn his entire life around.  The story behind the motto of "Lie, Cheat, and Steal" is talked about before the documentry ends on Eddie's crowning moment in winning the WWE Championship from Brock Lesnar.This DVD is Eddie Guerrero's story that was originally put together as a television special for the then-UPN network so the documentry itself is shorter than the normal length however the DVD itself is loaded with extra stories & outtakes such as the history of Gory Guerrero, Eddie fighting (and losing) to a monkey, how the Guerrero family were innovators of wrestling, and the history of Eddie & Chavo as partners.  Also hidden are bonus stories of Eddie talking about his tattoo, his first professional match, and Hector Guerrero & Gene Okerland reflecting on the Goobley Gooker's debut at Survivor Series '90 along with the highlight packages of the buildup leading into his matches against Dean Malenko, Survivor Series triple threat, and vs. Brock Lesnar.  Other bonus materials include 3 music videos, all the Los Guerreros vignettes, footage of J.B.L. giving Eddie's mom a heart attack, behind the scenes of the YJ Stinger ads along with the adds in both english & spanish, a look at Eddie on the cover of Low Rider magazine, his Outside The Ropes feature from Confidental, and a special look at his WrestleMania XX match.Bonus Matches Include:vs. Dean Malenko - This was not only their final match in their "Guerrero-Malekno" classic series but also their final match in ECW. This was also a 2 out of 3 match that honestly was perfectly booked & both men recieved a sendoff that any wrestler in the world would want. The match itself can't be put into words as it showcased why Dean & Eddie are classified as two of the greatest wrestlers at that time.Highlights of the alternative commentary between Eddie & Dean features talks about the ECW enviroment, the difference between each other now & then, their feelings heading towards WCW at the time, and a few jokes at each others expense.(ECW Hardcore TV)[Also available on "ECW: Path Of Destruction"]vs. WCW Crusierweight Champion Chris Jericho - For the longest time, this was a "lost classic" that kept getting overshadowed by the later crusierweight series of matches with Rey Mysterio but this was the defination of what the crusierweight division was in it's prime...fast paced high impact action with great inring mat wrestling wrestling & high flyin'.  Again, a lost classic that finally gets the justice it deserves.(WCW Fall Brawl '97)Mask vs. Title: WCW Crusierweight Championship vs. Rey Mysterio Jr. - Most peopel concider this the best match in WCW crusierweight history. The storytelling here was right on point with Eddie going after Rey's mask from time to time while showcasing the high flyin' & ground based lucha libre style. Classic match, no questions asked.Highlights from the alternative commentary with Rey & Eddie include the history behind the mask, the backstage problems with Eric Bischoff before the match, and both men's past in Mexico.(WCW Halloween Havoc '97)[Also available on both Rey Mysterio DVD's "619" & "Biggest Little Man"]Hair Match vs. Chavo Guerrero Jr. - Before this, you get a bonus "match" with Chavo vs. Stevie Ray from Harlem Heat.  This was Eddie & Chavo's best match as Chavo was playing mind games with Eddie throughout this competitive match with both men stealing each others finishers at times.(WCW Bash At The Beach '98)Ladder Match: WWE Intercontinental Championship vs. Rob Van Dam - This match had a style of both of them using the ladder to make their normal moves more high impact and was without a doubt one of the best matches on WWE TV for that year.Highlights of the alternative commentary with Eddie Guerrero & RVD featured RVD's most inspirational wrestlers along with both men comparing their own frog splashes.("WWE RAW" May '02)[Also available on "The Ladder Match"]with Chavo Guerrero vs. WWE Tag Team Champions Edge & Rey Mysterio vs. Chris Benoit & Kurt Angle - Without a doubt, match of the year for me. Very similar to the earlier crusierweight match with Jericho except it was a triple threat tag team match that defines the words "wrestling clinic" by all six men.(Survivor Series '02)WWE United States Championship Tournament Finals vs. Chris Benoit - Just like any other time they have gotten into the ring, this was a wrestling at it's finest here between both men with, of course, Eddie putting his own little twist on things with his comedic moments at times.  This was one of those matches that was so good, not even the ending took away from it.(Vengeance '03)vs. WWE Champion Brock Lesnar - Both men clicked & put on a great mat-based wrestling match with Brock just not being able to beat Eddie no matter what he throws at him to the point where's yelling "Just Die Eddie!". It's too bad Brock leaves a month later because I wanted to see a rematch between these two later on. Eddie didn't look inferior of the Lesnar & Goldberg's cameo didn't take away from the end result of Eddie winning the championship & going straight into the people to celebrate. Eddie Guerrero finally won the big one.(WWE No Way Out '04)[Also available on Eddie Guerrero's "Viva La Raza"]Other matches include a six man tag featuring the Guerrero family (Hector, Chavo, Mando Guerrero) & a young Cactus Jack along with a match from the AAA "When Worlds Collide" PPV featuring Guerrero teaming with Art Barr vs. Octagon & El Hijo Santo.In the end, this was a fitting celebration of the career for Eddie Guerrero at that time.  WWE has later released a 3 disc set full of more matches throughout his career but this is a perfect counterpiece to it as you won't get the entire story of Eddie Guerrero without both disc so this is one that should definatly be added to your collection if it isn't already there.  We Miss You Eddy.
summary: Remembering One Of The Greatest Of This Generation

reviewText: This DVD is an outstanding documentary that covers the wrestling life of one of the greatest WWE suerstars  and all his troubles with drugs and alcohol that ultimatley cost him his life. It was made before his untimely but predictable premature death. The title is ironic in many ways. The material is covered extensively by various customer reviewers so suffice to say that it is all here from his humble beginnings and royal wrestling roots , through his high school  years in El  Paso, his early career in Mexico and abroad in Japan, his associations with fellow wrestlers like Chris Benoit and Rey Mysterio and of course his cousin Chavo  and the rest of his wrestling family. His influence and impact cannot be denied, his legacy will remain in the annals of wrestling lore  and his place secure with his recent induction into the WWE Hall of Fame at Wrestlemania 22. The footage is excellent, especially the older footage that reveals a steroidless  physique. Only a few entertainers deaths have had affect on me (Lennon comes to mind) where I felt sad to the point of tears for someones death who is not known to me personally. Such was the case with Eddie Guerrero and the day I sat to watch wrestling with my son and the story of Eddies death was told in  the form of homages we both sat with tears welled up in our eyes. Although his death was months ago I  wanted more Eddie Guerrero everytime I tuned in wrestling. This disc had a catharsis effect on me because I wanted more of that great entertainer. He had a comedic talent that was matched by his skills and only overshadowed by his problems. He could play the heal to the tilt but you still had to love him for beneath that bad boy persona the real Eddie was always evident. Watching this disc was joyous because all his talents throughout his carrer are revealed for all his fans.  Who can forget the night he won the World Heavyweight Title and his embrace of Chris Benoit? Eddie will be missed but there is this fine disc for you to enjoy when you feel like seeing that  Eddie look and the cry of Viva La Raza from the legion of fans. If you are a fan of Eddie Gueereo than you have to have this disc, go ahead and buy it, you won't be dissapointed. Eddie Guerreo lives on in each of our hearts and on this DVD. RIP Eddie G.

reviewText: This release came out over a year before Eddie's untimely passing. While a bit short for my tastes (just under an hour, it should've been as long as Chris Benoit's was), it was still very good."Cheating Death, Stealing Life" is a tale of Eddie Guerrero's beginnings in Mexico as a kid in a wrestling family, from meeting and marrying Vickie, to his wrestling career from Mexico's AAA, New Japan, ECW, WCW and WWE. It goes into his highs professionally to his lows personally. His fall from grace due to his addiction to drugs and alcohol, losing his job with WWE in 2001 and nearly losing his marriage and family.It is also a story about coming full circle and redemption as he got his life back together, ending with him winning the WWE Title from Brock Lesner in 2004 and being one of the main events at WrestleMania XX!I am not a real sentimental guy but I found myself shaking my head and nearly crying on some parts. Seeing the way Vickie loved him and the way Eddie knows he hurt her and many people with his problems made me sad but also happy that he did turn his life around. The parts showing himself and Chris Benoit also made me sad as well. Two very talented performers who ended life so very differently. Even though it seems now that Chris' actions may not have been entirely his fault, its still sad. Benoit DID say one true thing on here though, he said that "this is a story that needs to be told." I couldn't agree more.On a personal note, let me say this. IF Chris somehow is in heaven, I only hope Eddie is there to comfort him and his family that he killed because I feel that Eddie IS in heaven!Back to the DVD, there is only a small amount of matches BUT they do show how brilliant Eddie was in the ring. The other extras are very fun and good too.Eddie Guerrero, may you rest in peace!Eddie GuerreroOctober 9, 1967 - November 13, 2005

reviewText: You really can't say enough about the story of Eddie Guerrero.  This DVD contains an awesome documentary that takes you on a trip through a life that fought demons and WON.  A truly inspiring story that will hold your attention from beginning to end.  Even non wrestling fans will have no choice but to respect and appreciate the life of Eddie Guerrero.  Also included are matches that span his entire career from AAA to ECW to WCW to WWE.  If you enjoyed Hard Knocks:  The Chris Benoit Story, you are going to love Cheating Death, Stealing Life.

reviewText: -Eddie Guerrero, what else can be said about one of the greatest wrestlers that was taken from us all too soon. Well this DVD (released almost 2 years ago, by the way) shows us a look inside his rise to wrestling fame and the obstacles he suffered and overcame. The documentary is only about 45 mins. long (it's the UPN special, minus the commercials), but it's very informative and at times moving.-The documentary shows his childhood, his love for low riders, his marriage to Vicki right after his father Gory's death, his career start in wrestling, his car accident, his overdose afterwards, his Latino Heat character in WWF, his addiction gets really bad, then loses his job and his marriage, his rise up, the Los Guerreros, his Lie, Cheat, & Steal character, the origins of the frogsplash, and his title win at No Way Out.-The DVD shows his days growing up in El Paso, TX, meeting his wife, his career in WCW, his drug and alcohol addictions and much more. This DVD though shows that anyone can change if they believe it enough, as Eddie overcame his addiction and achieved even greater success in WWE.There are 10 matches on this DVD set including:-AWA Superclash III-12/13/88-Six-Man Tag Team Match: Hector (Eddie), Chavo (Sr.) and Mando Guerrero vs. Cactus Jack, & The Rock 'n' Roll RPM's: Nice to see Eddie and Cactus Jack (Mick Foley) in the early part of their careers, man Cactus was slim back then. The match itself was pretty good, nice high flying by the Guerreros. Guerreros win in about 6 1/2 mins. 7/10.-When World's Collide-11/6/94-2 out of 3 Falls Hair vs. Mask Match: w/Love Machine (Art Barr) vs. Octagon & El Hijo Santo:  Done in elimination style, you must beat both men to get the fall for your team. A good high flying match, sick frankensteiner by Guerrero from the top while Barr held Santo on his shoulders and a very nice double suicide dive by Octagon & Santo to the outside. There was a nice amount of wrestling holds and Guerrero & Machine win the first fall, but Octagon & Santo win the next two falls, in about 22 mins. so Barr & Guerrero both lose their hair. 8/10.-ECW-8/26/95-2 out of 3 Falls Match: vs. Dean Malenko: Nice emotion from the fans chanting "please don't go" to both men, as both were going to WCW after this event. The match was pretty good, fast paced and well done. Eddie wins the first fall with a roll-up, Dean wins the second fall via tap out with the Texas Cloverleaf and as for the third fall both men's shoulders were down so it was declared a draw after about 20 mins. 8/10. Includes alternate commentary by both men.-WCW Fall Brawl-9/14/97-Crusierweight Title Match vs. Chris Jericho (Champion): Good match, great action and plenty of high flying, with some good wrestling holds. Eddie wins with the frog splash in about 17 mins. to become the new Crusierweight Champion. 8/10.(Available on Breaking the Code: Behind the Walls of Chris Jericho)-WCW Halloween Havoc-10/26/97-Crusierweight Title Mask vs. Title: vs. Rey Mysterio: What a fast paced, great match. The timing of these two couldn't have been better. Rey pulls off a sick flip off of the top rope into a DDT on Eddie, great move. I can't really say much more about it, just watch and enjoy. Rey wins in about 14 mins. to become the Crusierweight title. 11/10. Includes alternate commentary by both men.(Available on Wrestling's Highest Flyers & Rey Mysterio: Biggest Little Man)-Bash at the Beach-7/12/98-Hair vs. Hair Match: vs. Chavo Jr.: This started out as Chavo vs. Stevie Ray, which was a quick tune-up (hehe), Chavo quickly gave up to let Stevie win. Chavo was a bit weird as this character, a goofy nephew loved idolized his uncle Eddie. This was a bit of a weird one after some anitcs by Chavo for a few mins, Eddie starts beating down Chavo, but he comes back on Eddie with some quick offense. Eddie wins with a small package in about 12 mins. Postmatch stuff with Chavo shaving his own head was weird but funny. 6/10.-Monday Night Raw-5/27/02-Ladder Match for the Intercontinental Title vs. Rob Van Dam: Great match, lots of uses of the ladder, another one that's hard to describe, better to watch. Rolling Thunder by RVD onto Eddie under the ladder was awesome to watch. RVD wins in about 18 1/2 mins. 10/10. Includes alternate commentary from both men.(Available on Ladder Match)-Survivor Series-11/17/02-Triple Threat Elimination Match for the WWE Tag Team Titles: w/Chavo vs. Kurt Angle & Chris Benoit vs. Edge and Rey Mysterio (Champions): Great fast paced match, all six men get in equal amounts of offense. Edge spears Benoit to eliminate his team in about 13 mins., then Eddie locks in the Laso from El Paso on Rey to win the match and the titles in about 19 mins. 9/10.-Vengeance-7/23/03-Finals of the U.S. Title Tournament vs. Chris Benoit: Great match, great wrestling holds, though the finish takes away from it a bit when Rhyno turns on Benoit and gives him a vicous gore, then Eddie hits the frog splash for the win in about 22 mins. The antics from Eddie throughout the match were funny. 9/10.-No Way Out-2/15/04-WWE Title Match vs. Brock Lesnar: You could hear and actually feel the fans pulling for Eddie throughout the match. Great match, really long too. Brock beat on Eddie for quite a bit, but Eddie kept coming back with tons of wrestling holds, including lots of submission moves on the right knee. There was a major league pop for Eddie when he locked on an STF on Brock. Great match overall by both men and thanks to his passion and a timely spear by Goldberg on Brock, Eddie countered the F-5 by Brock into a DDT, then hit the frog splash on Brock to win his first (and sadly only) WWE Title in about 30 mins. 10/10.(Available on Viva La Raza: The Legacy of Eddie Guerrero)This is truly a great DVD for wrestling and Eddie fans, great matches (some classic), great insight and funny extras (watch and laugh). The Los Guerreros vignettes are hilarious, the YJ Stinger stuff is good, all the extras are fun to watch. This is a fantastic DVD purchase. R.I.P. Eddie you will be missed, but not forgotten.
summary: Documentary is good, the matches and extras are better....

reviewText: For DVD addicts like myself, here is the skinny on Eddie Guerrero's double-disc release for September:Of course, the 45-Minute 'Cheating Death, Stealing Life' program, also known as 'The Eddie Guerrero Story' which aired on UPN earlier this year.SIX-MAN TAG MATCH: Los Guerreros vs. Cactus Jack & Rock n Roll RPM's (AWA SuperClash III- December 13, 1988)HAIR VERSUS MASKS: Los Gringos (Eddie Guerrero & Art Barr) vs. El Hijo del Santo & Octagon (AAA When Worlds Collide- November 6, 1994)BEST OF THREE FALLS: Eddie Guerrero vs. Dean Malenko (ECW- August 26, 1995)WCW CRUISERWEIGHT CHAMPIONSHIP: Eddie Guerrero vs. Chris Jericho (WCW Fall Brawl- September 14, 1997)TITLE VERSUS MASK: Eddie Guerrero vs. Rey Mysterio (WCW Halloween Havoc- October 26, 1997)HAIR VERSUS HAIR: Eddie Guerrero vs. Chavo Guerrero Jr. (WCW Bash at the Beach- July 12, 1998)WWE INTERCONTINENTAL LADDER MATCH: Eddie Guerrero vs. Rob Van Dam (Monday Night Raw- May 27, 2002)ELIMINATION MATCH: Rey Mysterio & Edge vs. Kurt Angle & Chris Benoit vs. Los Guerreros (WWE Survivor Series 2002- November 17, 2002)U.S. TITLE TOURNAMENT FINALS: Eddie Guerrero vs. Chris Benoit (WWE Vengeance- July 27, 2003)WWE CHAMPIONSHIP: Eddie Guerrero vs. Brock Lesnar (WWE No Way Out- February 15, 2004)Not a bad line-up as it covers a little bit of everything from his career, and (fortunately) it does not duplicate anything on previous releases, specifically matches on 'Hard Knocks: The Chris Benoit Story.'

reviewText: ----The Wal-Mart in my Town goofed and put this on the shelf on the 14 Sep 04 the day SummerSlam 2004 was pulled by WWE due to Audio problems, so I have had this DVD for 10 days now and have finished it. Like I said I am far from an Eddie Fan, his personal choices he as made in his life makes him the farthest from a role model as you can get. I do not think he should have been rewarded the WWE Title, in my view the U.S. Championship could have be his top singles title and I would not dislike Eddie as much. Hell Al Snow has been doing this just as long, is Vince going to grant him a World Title run, NO, he will not, but Snow can entertain and wrestle just as well so why not.----Some may call Eddie's choices "Personal Demons". One Driving While Intoxicated and he totaled a car while Driving Under the Influence; he was on some medication that it is not recommended to operate a vehicle while taking. One DWI(alcohol) and one DUI(prescribed drug), what if he killed someone, I can not look past those two particular choices he made. He lost his job with WWE (He did get it back, Vince is a forgiving man, that does give chances, hell he took Hogan back) he almost lost his family (His wife is forgiving, from what I can tell she is a wonderful women). You can't call them Personal Demons when they effect your job, family/friends, and any pedestrian that could have been killed any one of those two driving choices. I would call them Public Demons.----This is not all bad, I will give Eddie his dues, he fought his demons, he did not kill anyone, he got his job back, kept his family in tact, hence he Cheated Death, and He is Stealing Life. I can respect him for owning up to his bad decisions, It takes a big man to come out and admit wrong doing, his penance has included having his "Real Life Past" exploited in storylines on SMACKDOWN! and on PPVs by both family (Chavo) as well as some of the boys in the locker room (Hymen, Show, and Angle), and he can no longer consume alcohol, he knows he can not stop at just a few so he does not have even one. So the fact that he lets his real life be worked in makes him a real man.----I hope the opinions I have expressed are taken as just that opinions. I made some harsh statements however I come right around and give him props as well, I am able to see two sides of this issue, bad choices great redemption.----I have not found any Easter Eggs. This does not mean they don't exist, however I have not found them yet.---Disk One--45 min Eddie Bio, 13 Chapters, Growing up, Low Riders, Marries Vicky and Gory Dies, Career Begins, Car Accident (DUI), Overdose, Latino Heat, Problems Get Worse, Rock Bottom (DWI), Starting Over, Lie, Cheat, Steal, FrogSplash, No Way Out.--Extra Matches--AWA SuperClash III-1988 Chi-Town, Hector, Chavo, and Mando (Eddie) vs. Cactus Jack and Rock `n' Roll RPM's--When Worlds Collide-1994 LA, Hair vs. Mask, Eddie/Love Machine vs. Octagon/ El Hijo Santo--ECW-1995 Philly, 2 Out Of 3 Falls, vs. Dean Malenko (Commentary with Eddie and Dean)--WCW Fall Brawl-1997 Winston Salem, Cruiserweight Title Match vs. Jericho--WCW Halloween Havoc-1997 Las Vegas, Mask vs. Cruiserweight Title Match, vs. Rey (Commentary with Eddie and Rey)--Los Guerreros' Vignettes- Baby Carriage/Pool/Low Rider/Golf/Valet--Music Videos-Finger Eleven "One Thing"/Seether "Gasoline"/ Soil "Redefine"---Disk Two--Extra Matches--Bash at the Beach-1998 San Diego Hair vs. Hair vs. Chavo--WWE RAW-2002, Edmonton IC Ladder Match vs. RVD (Commentary with Eddie and RVD)--WWE Survivor Series-2002 MSG Triple Threat Tag Team Match Eddie/Chavo vs. Angle/Benoit vs. Edge/Rey--WWE Vengeance-2003, Denver US Title Match vs. Benoit--WWE No Way Out-2003 San Francisco WWE Title Match vs. Lesnar--Eddie's mother has a Heart Attack 2004 SMACKDOWN!--Confidential Behind-The-Scenes YJ Stinger/ YJ Stinger Spot English/Spanish/Behind-The-Scenes Low Rider Magazine/Outside the Ropes/Eddie Guerrero Celebration--Special Extras Gory Guerrero/Eddie vs. The Monkey/Moonsault/Fighting for Honor/Injury (Elbow dislocation from FrogSplash First WWE Match)/Los Guerreros/WMXX----All in all a four star DVD and coming from a person that went into this DVD not liking Eddie, I'd say most WWE fans would like this DVD.
summary: I'm not a big Eddie Fan But this is a good Set

reviewText: Cheating Death, Stealing life was originally a documentary that showed on UPN and now it's on DVD. This DVD tells the story of Eddie Guerrero from his rise in the ranks of pro wrestling (WCW, ECW, WWE) to his car accident to his 3 OD's to his win at No way out 2004 to win the wwe title. This DVD is a great DVD with material not shown on the original brodcast of the special. Extras include the WWE Championship match at No Way Out against Brock. His match with Rey Mysterio for the crusierweight title at WCW Halloween Havoc '97 (One of the best matches in 97) all in all this was a great DVD but I wish they would have had his match at WM XX against Angle. My Favorite match personally. If you like eddie or are a big fan you should get this dvd.

reviewText: I have watched wrestling for a pretty decent length of time. I enjoy hearing and seeing the real life instances and struggles that these guys (and ladies) endure to make their dreams come true.Out of all the releases lately, Eddie Guerrero has one of the most emotional stories. It has some great ups, and some incredible obstacles to overcome as the downs. The documentary portion of the disc is actually better than the extras, which these days are hard to do.After watching this story about Eddie Guerrero, you can see even now not only the legacy he feels he needs to live up to, but how every day is a struggle to stay off booze and drugs. And considering what these guys do day in and day out physically, it truly is amazing.I never watched WCW, but I knew of Eddie Guerrero. When the Radicals showed up in the WWF, I was ecstatic. Right away I was a fan and I have been enjoying his in-ring action ever since. It's just to bad that business is the way it is and there is currently no longer a spot for Eddie as WWE champion. He is a great performer and needs to be at nothing more than the top spot. His matches lately vs. Kurt Angle are nothing short of classics and I only see more great matches from Eddie down the road.The extras are pretty good. Not as many as I would have hoped. I always enjoy RAW's and Smackdown matches on these DVD over the PPV matches. Not everyone has every TV show on tape, but true fans usually have the PPV's on tape or own the DVD's. I enjoyed how many of the matches had alternate commentary from the performers. One of the better ones is the commentary during the Rey Mysterio match. They actually added insight to the match and reflected on their careers during that time. Another really good one was during the Eddie/Malenko match. I wish Dean were given a better chance to shine as a wrestler during his stint in the WWE.The highlights of the extras are:VS. Chris JerichoVS. Rob Van Dam (Ladder Match)VS. Rey MysterioVs. Dean Malenko (Final night in ECW)In addition to the matches the Los Guerrero skits are all here as are extra stories from the documentary are included.If there were one complaint, it would be that there are no New Japan matches included; I felt there should have been at least one.Overall a very good DVD collection and a great addition to your WWE catalogue, especially if you are an Eddie fan.
summary: A Story that deserves to be told and worth telling!

reviewText: The Eddie Guerrero story is a surprisingly well done documentary of a 17 year veteran who dealt with the demons on the outside, and more importantly, the demons on the inside. It goes on to tell how Eddie overdosed on drugs more than once, and when he got into a near fatal car accident, only to fight back and eventually win the wwe championship in a triumphant victory.The documentary is touching and inspiring, not to mention it is willing to throw in several funny moments and jokes that his relatives share with us. This is a great story and should be viewed by anyone who wants to know what its like for a Mexican wrestler and the different styles that the lucha libre brings to the world.As for the extras, well, they are off the hook as well:Disk One:Hector, Chavo, and Mando Guerrero vs. Cactus Jack, and the Rock and Roll RPM's: Now when I say this match is old school, I mean it! Lets go back 16 years, to where even Mick Foley wasn't that well known and you have this decent six man tag team match. Eddie isn't in this, I think he is somewhere in his early teen years, but this is definately not bad of a match. Old School fans will enjoy this one.  7.5/10Hair vs. Mask, Eddie Guerrero and Love Machine vs. Octagon and El Hijo Santo: This is another old match, 10 years ago, when masks and titles are on the line in this one. A back and forth battle, Eddie shows us how he wrestled when he was a rookie and how much he has changed nowadays. A good match. 8/102 out of 3 falls, Eddie Guerrero vs. Dean Malenko: Now this is probably the one match in ECW that was just the purest wrestling you will ever see. I think this was the last match these two would have in ECW. A great technical battle and should be viewed by rookie wrestlers who want a few tips. 9/10Eddie Guerrero vs. Chris Jericho: Very cool to see Jericho when he was still in WCW. A good match, some intense submission holds and lots of mat wrestling. Jericho is great and so is eddie. But why was there another ring next to the one they were using? Leave it to WCW to make things confusing. Anyway still a good match. 7.5/10WCW Crusierweight Championship, Eddie vs. Rey Mysterio: The only good thing about WCW was the fact that they had the best crusierweights in the world. Rey and Eddie put on a fantastic show that had Rey's famous mask against Eddie's belt. A back and forth battle that had both men show off their skills. Eddie almost even ripped the mask off during the match. A great match that wont be forgotten. 9.5/10Other extras have five short segments of Eddie and Chavo goofing off and have good times with: A woman and her baby, an old lady who needs her pool "cleaned," two preppy guys and thier hot gal pals!, two guys on the golf course, and a unfortunate man who gives them his car because he thought they were valet boys!Plus three music videos; Finger Eleven-"One thing," Seether-"Gasoline," and Soil-"Redefine"DISK 2:Hair vs. Hair, Eddie vs. Chavo Jr: Now this was a very "interesting match" Chavo seemed to lose it at the end and starts to shave off his own hair and kept telling Eddie that they could be twins if he wanted. Yeah, kinda creepy. But anyway a funny match in some spots. 7.5/10Ladder Match for the Intercontinental championship: Now this was a good ladder match between Eddie and RVD. Two ladders and a chair was used in this in some very hard hitting moves. Eddie powerbombed RVD off the ladder, RVd gave Eddie a kick which sent the chair into eddie's face. A scary moment though when Eddie fell off the ladder and almost fell on one of the legs on the floor, and when RVd lost his balance and fell as well. A great ladder match. 9/10Triple Threat Match at Survivor series '02: A good triple threat match between the Guerreros, Benoit and Angle, and Mysterio and Edge. Second best match of that ppv that night. Eddie and Guerrero won the titles and thats where the whole LIE CHEAT STEAL motto started in my opinion. An excellent tag match, though slow in some spots. 8.5/10US title tournament finals, Eddie vs. Benoit at Vengeance 03: A great technical battle that has Eddie up to his old tricks again. He stole and cheated his way to victory, but that is what we should expect nowadays, right? A good match. 8/10Eddie vs. Lesnar, No Way Out 04: Finally, after five months of listening to Lesnar brag all the time, eddie finally dethrones the former youngest wwe champion ever! A match that showed the little guy can always pick up a victory if your not careful! Good match and the celebration afterwards was awsome! 10/10The extras have: Eddie's mother has a heart attack! Confidential moments: YJ stinger commercial of eddie and the party he had. A behind the scenes shot of a low rider commercial, and several interviews with relatives. Plus a look at his match at WM 20 and how the Guerreros lie cheat steal thing got started.Finally, this is a DVd worth your money, lots of extras and some great matches, plus a great story equals a ten star DVd!
summary: Think of it as every star is = to two stars

reviewText: Even though he unfortunately passed away last year, Eddie Guerrero will ALWAYS live in the mind of wrestling fans worldwide. He may have had his demons outside of the right, but inside of the squared circle, Eddie could perform with ANYONE. He did it with style and grace, and this 2 DVD set highlights why. Here's my review of the matches:Disc 1Hector, Chavo & Mando Guerrero vs. Cactus Jack & Rock 'n' Roll RPMs (AWA Superclash III - Chicago, Ill. - 12/13/1988), **1/2 (A fairly decent match here.)Hair vs. Mask: Eddie Guerrero & Art Barr vs. El Hijo Del Santo & Octagon (When Worlds Collide - Los Angeles, Cal. - 11/6/1994), ***** (Yep, our first Match of the Year candidate here. Just all around awesomeness here.)2 Out of 3 Falls: Eddie Guerrero vs. Dean Malenko (ECW - Philadelphia, Penn. - 8/26/1995), ****1/2 (Both of these men were on there way to WCW, as this match serves as their ECW swan song. What a great way to go out on.)Alternate Commentary by Dean Malenko and Eddie GuerreroWCW Cruiserweight Title: Eddie Guerrero vs. Chris Jericho (WCW Fall Brawl - Winstom-Salem, N.C. - 9/14/1997), ****1/4 (A classic match between these two in the opening match, which was the usually case for a WCW event back in those days.)Mask vs. Title - WCW Cruiserweight Title: Eddie Guerrero vs. Rey Mysterio (WCW Halloween Havoc - Las Vegas, Nev. - 10/26/1997), ***** (Another Match of the Year candidate. This was one of WCW's best matches ever, as it was also the best match for both of these athletes.)Alternate Commentary by Eddie Guerrero and Rey MysterioDisc 2Hair vs. Hair: Eddie Guerrero vs. Chavo Guerrero (WCW Bash at the Beach - San Diego, Cal. - 7/12/1998), ** (Not one of their finest moments to be sure. Could've been a lot more, but they were hampered with a ridiculous storyline @ this point in 1998 WCW.)Ladder Match - Intercontinental Title: Eddie Guerrero vs. Rob Vam Dam (RAW - Edmonton, Alberta - 5/27/2002), ****3/4 (A totally awesome match, one of the greatest matches in the history of RAW. The ONLY reason this match is NOT 5 stars is the fact that RVD tried the frog splash FROM THE TOP OF THE LADDER, but he sadly blew the spot.)Alternate Commentary by Eddie Guerrero and Rob Van DamTriple-Threat Elimination Match - WWE Tag Team Titles: Eddie & Chavo Guerrero vs. Kurt Angle & Chris Benoit vs. Edge & Rey Mysterio (WWE Survivor Series - New York City, N.Y. - 11/17/2002), ***1/2 (We hit a match that should've been a 5 star match, but the storyline here was starting to wear thin @ that point. It was still very good though.)Finals of WWE U.S. Title Tournament: Eddie Guerrero vs. Chris Benoit (WWE Vengeance - Denver, Col. - 7/27/2003), **** (Guerrero captures the US title here in an excellent match with Benoit.)WWE Championship Title: Eddie Guerrero vs. Brock Lesner (WWE No Way Out - San Francisco, Cal. - 2/15/2004), ****1/4 (I was surprised when Eddie won the title on this night. They delivered a truly awesome match here that entertained.)Easter EggsEaster Egg: Hector Guerrero Discusses the Gobbledy GookerHow To Access: On Disc One, Go to Extras. Click left on AWA Superclash and the clip will playEaster Egg: Eddie Guerrero vs. Dean MalenkoHow To Access: On Disc One, Go to Extras. Click left on ECW and a video on the classic Malenko vs. Guerrero feud will playEaster Egg: Triple Threat Tag VideoHow To Access: On Disc Two, Go to Extras. Click left twice on WWE Survivor Series and a video promoting the Benoit & Angle vs. Los Guerreros vs. Edge & Mysterio bout will play.Easter Egg: Eddie Guerrero vs. Brock LesnarHow To Access: On Disc Two, Go to Extras. Click left twice on No Way Out and a video on Lesnar vs. Guerrero will play.Easter Egg: Eddie Guerrero's first MatchHow To Access: In the Extras Session, click left on Fighting for Honor. A clip of Guerrrero discussing his first ever match will play. .Easter Egg: Eddie's tattooHow To Access: On Special Extras, click left twice on Injury. Eddie will discuss the cross tattoo on his left arm.Overall, what we have here is another awesome DVD set, this time about the late great Eddie Guerrero. Another high recommendation for this legend.R.I.P. Eddie Guerrero

reviewText: In November 2005, Eddie Guerrero was found dead in his hotel room, the victim of what appeared to be an undiagnosed heart problem. He was 38 years old. The resulting outpouring from the wrestling community was something the extent of which hadn't been seen since the death of Owen Hart in 1999, and showed the tremendous amount of love and respect people had for this man. One look at "Cheating Life, Stealing Death" and it's easy to see why, as Eddie Guerrero's incredible story is documented in this excellent two disc DVD set.The story starts at the very beginning, during Eddie's childhood. The son of pro wrestling legend Gory Guerrero, and growing up around three brothers who were all wrestlers, the sport was in his blood and it was almost inevitable that Eddie would grow up to embark on a career in the squared circle. From his days of wrestling with his nephew Chavo (only three years his junior) as a child during intermissions at shows promoted by his father, to his first pro matches, through his days in AAA, ECW and WCW and eventual arrival in WWE, it's all covered in the documentary, and supported with interviews with family and friends, and archive footage (thanks to WWE's extensive tape library). As can be expected, much of the documentary focusses on Guerrero's fall from grace and descent into the world of alcoholism and narcotic use. The story documented here shows why Guerrero was, and is one of the most loved and respected people in the business, as Guerrero's rise back to the top was nothing short of incredible. The story is truly uplifting and put across extremely well by WWE. It should be noted that the story ends in early 2004, as the DVD was released some time before Guerrero's untimely death.For me, the extras are generally the most important part of a wrestling DVD of this nature, and they do not disappoint. His life story aside, Guerrero was without a doubt one of the finest performers to ever set foot in a ring, and we're presented with a wealth of incredible matches from the first 15 or so years of his career. Among them are the legendary Hair vs. Mask tag team match from AAA's When Worlds Collide pay-per-view in 1994, featuring Guerrero and the late "Love Machine" Art Barr taking on Octagon and El Hijo De Santo under Lucha Libre rules, his classic 2/3 falls encounter with Dean Malenko from ECW, the 1997 Match Of The Year candidate again Rey Mysterio Jr. at Halloween Havoc and his emotionally charged WWE championship bout with Brock Lesnar at No Way Out 2004, in addition to many more great matches. In addition to being one of the finest wrestlers, Guerrero was also incredibly charismatic, and the hilarious vignettes used to hype the Los Guerreros tag team (featuring Eddie and nephew Chavo) are among the highlights of the extras, as well as anecdotes told by members and friends of the Guerrero family.Eddie Guerrero's story is a genuinely inspiring tale of a man who had everything, lost it all and was able to bounce back even better than he had been before, and "Cheating Life, Stealing Death" tells the story perfectly. WWE have once again put out a fantastic DVD set, made all the more enjoyable by the story that it tells. The documentary is well put together, and the selection of extras is well above average, in both actual selection and quality. This is a must buy for any past fan of Guerrero or anyone who never had the pleasure of experiencing some of the man's finer moments.
summary: The Story Of A True Legend
